{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Callouts are an important part of the typing experience, where input callouts show the currently pressed character and action callouts show secondary actions when certain keys are long pressed.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has ways to automatically show an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Callouts\/InputCallout","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" when the user types, and has a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/CalloutActionProvider","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" that can provide actions that can be presented in an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Callouts\/ActionCallout","type":"reference"},{"text":" when long pressing certain keys.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"👑 ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardKitPro","type":"reference"},{"text":" unlocks localized providers for all locales. Information about Pro features can be found at the end of this article.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Callout namespace","anchor":"Callout-namespace"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit has a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Callouts"},{"text":" namespace that has callout-related types and views. For instance, an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Callouts\/InputCallout"},{"type":"text","text":" can present the currently pressed character while an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Callouts\/ActionCallout"},{"type":"text","text":" can present secondary actions while long pressing a key."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Callout-context","type":"heading","text":"Callout context"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit has an observable ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/CalloutContext","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" class that provides observable input and action callout state, such as the currently pressed key or the callout actions to present."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit automatically creates an instance of this class and injects it into ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardInputViewController\/state"},{"text":", then updates this context when keys are pressed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Callout action providers","type":"heading","anchor":"Callout-action-providers","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In KeyboardKit, a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/CalloutActionProvider"},{"text":" can be used to provide dynamic callout actions, which are then presented when a key that has actions defined in the provider is long pressed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit automatically creates an instance of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Callouts\/StandardActionProvider","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and injects it into "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardInputViewController\/services","isActive":true},{"text":". You can replace it at any time, as described further down, or inject localized providers into it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"How to show input and action callouts","type":"heading","anchor":"How-to-show-input-and-action-callouts"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can apply a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/SwiftUI\/View\/keyboardCalloutContainer(calloutContext:keyboardContext:)","isActive":true},{"text":" view extension to make any view act as the container of input and action callouts:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["MyKeyboard()","    .keyboardCalloutContainer(...)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This will bind a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/CalloutContext","isActive":true},{"text":" to the view, then apply ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Callouts\/ActionCallout","isActive":true},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Callouts\/InputCallout"},{"type":"text","text":" views that show as this context changes. There are also separate input and action-specific container extensions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are also individual extensions for "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/SwiftUI\/View\/keyboardActionCalloutContainer(calloutContext:keyboardContext:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/SwiftUI\/View\/keyboardInputCalloutContainer(calloutContext:keyboardContext:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/SystemKeyboard"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Keyboard\/Button","isActive":true},{"text":" will automatically apply the proper extensions and update the context as you interact with them.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"How-to-create-a-custom-callout-action-provider","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"How to create a custom callout action provider"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can create a custom ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/CalloutActionProvider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" to customize which callout actions to present for certain "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardAction"},{"type":"text","text":"s."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can implement "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/CalloutActionProvider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" from scratch, or inherit and customize the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Callouts\/StandardActionProvider","isActive":true},{"text":". For instance, here’s a custom callout action provider that inherits ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Callouts\/StandardActionProvider","isActive":true},{"text":" and customizes the actions for the $ key:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["class CustomCalloutActionProvider: Callout.StandardActionProvider {","    ","    override func calloutActions(for action: KeyboardAction) -> [KeyboardAction] {","        switch action {","        case .character(let char):","            switch char {","            case \"$\": return \"$₽¥€¢£₩\".chars.map { KeyboardAction.character($0) }","            default: break","            }","        default: break","        }","        return super.calloutActions(for: action)","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To use this provider instead of the standard one, just inject it into "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardInputViewController\/services"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["class KeyboardViewController: KeyboardInputViewController {","","    override func viewDidLoad() {","        services.calloutActionProvider = CustomCalloutActionProvider()","        super.viewDidLoad()","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This will make KeyboardKit use your custom implementation instead of the standard one.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Views","anchor":"Views","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Callouts","isActive":true},{"text":" namespace has callout-specific views, that can be used to mimic the native iOS & iPadOS input and action callouts.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"tabs":[{"title":"Action Callout","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Callouts\/ActionCallout","type":"reference"},{"text":" view mimics a 